hat nutrient levels and grain yield decline with excessive weeding but less so if dung is applied. Manuring is an alternative for fallowing rather than replacing it because additional constrains crop up with prolonged cultivation: the population of coprophage insects was reduced so some dung stayed unconsumed, and extremely sandy soils developed because wind erosion had carried off the most fertile particles from these rather bare soils making manure input no longer effective.},
